The paper deals with deep neural network architecture for automatic thoracic disease detection on chest X-rays. The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and routing-by agreement mechanism in the architecture. The paper also discusses the use of Gradient-weighted Class Activation Mapping (Grad-CAM) for localization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of routing-by agreement mechanism, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of localization, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
